Weather Satisfactory for Russia Crops Up to June 20, Center Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-06-14T14:56:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/weather-satisfactory-for-russia-crops-up-to-june-20-center-says.html
Weather will be “mainly
satisfactory” for Russian crops in most of the country’s
European zone and “predominantly satisfactory” in the bulk of
Russian Asia until June 20, the country’s forecaster said on its
 website .  “Agro-meteorological conditions will be mainly
satisfactory for growth, and harvest formation of the majority
of agricultural crops on dominant territory in  Russia ’s European
part,” Hydrometeorological Centre of Russia said in its
forecast for the second ten days of June.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow 
